# What does NOT ship in the published .vsix.
#
# Sources, tests, tooling, CI, and docs are all excluded. The out/ directory is
# an ALLOWLIST: only the compiled runtime ships — test bundles, coverage,
# mutation/chaos artifacts and source maps stay out (a local out/ polluted by a
# test run must never bloat the package).
.vscode/**
.git/**
.github/**
.claude/**
node_modules/**
src/**
test/**
docs/**
scripts/**
examples/**
CONTEXT.md
tsconfig.json
esbuild.mjs
esbuild.test.mjs
eslint.config.mjs
stryker.conf.json
.gitignore
.vscodeignore
package-lock.json
*.vsix
*.log
media/shots/**
README.zh-CN.md

# out/ allowlist — exclude everything, then re-include only the runtime esbuild
# emits (extension host bundle, webview bundle + KaTeX CSS, lazy Mermaid bundle,
# and the KaTeX font files the CSS url()s resolve to).
**/*.map
out/**
!out/extension.js
!out/webview.js
!out/webview.css
!out/mermaid.js
!out/*.woff2
!out/*.woff
!out/*.ttf
